<section id="To_set_the_Image_Type_for_an_ISO_Image1" remap="TID_15515">
	<title>Setting the Image Type for an ISO Image</title>
	<para>
		The following procedure sets the image type for an ISO image.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Set the Image Type for an ISO Image</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Infrastructure</guimenu><guisubmenu>PXE</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the <guilabel>ISO Datastores</guilabel> accordion, and select the image that you want to set a type for.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guilabel>(Configuration)</guilabel>, then 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1851.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guilabel>(Edit this ISO Image)</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				From the <guilabel>Basic Information</guilabel> area, select the correct <guilabel>Type</guilabel>.
			</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/2323.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guilabel>Save</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>